Kubernetes Service Account 

Service Account is a identity used by pod to communicate cluster external services securely 

For example Requirement : for pod to communicate to S3 
My Pod want to communicate s3 so here s3 is outside kubernetes service we have always to enable communication to s3

1.
BY using node iam role and can communicate s3 by using background network communication

Node level IAM role help to enable authentication but how to implement connection between pod and s3

Pod --> node ENI --> Route table --> IG -> S3 

if you create vpc endpoint request flow like below 

Pod --> node ENI -->VPC  Route table --> VPC Endpoint  -> S3 


and connection purpose we are using above 2 flows

By using Node role above pod can authenticate s3

so the main drawback of node level role is along with required pods other pods also communicate with s3along with required pod also as permissions apply node role level which is not recommeneded by using service account we can 
allow permission to specific pod only instead of using node level IAM role.


SO in this case to overcome above we have serviceaccount concept 
